data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 15, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104bmh1665703174219.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bmh1665703174219.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bmh1665703174219.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bmh1665703174219\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"bmh1665703174219__security_driver_entry_point_431423\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">A customized security driver must include the <span class=\"ph filepath\">zsecdrv.h</span> and specify a function to serve as an entry point for the driver. Depending on the type of security driver, other definition files should also be included.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"bmh1665703174219__topic_d131966e1_d131967e1_d131968e1\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104bmh1665703174219_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"bmh1665703174219__codeblock_jkx_swj_dwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">#include \"zsecdrv.h\"\n#include \"usmtpsecsub.h\"\n#include \"unistr.h\"\n#include \"unienc.h\"\nextern long <var class=\"keyword varname\">EntryPointFunction</var>(USecDrv *SecDrv)</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bmh1665703174219__topic_d93707e1_d93708e1_d93709e1_d93710e1_d93711e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d285372e61\">Parameters</h2>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"bmh1665703174219__parml_hm3_5wj_dwb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\">EntryPointFunction</dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">For SMTP security drivers, this can be any name. For a client/server security\n                  driver, it must be <code class=\"ph codeph\">usecappl()</code>.</dd>\n</dl>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"4\" id=\"bmh1665703174219__table_d15743e1_d15744e1_d15745e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bmh1665703174219__table_d15743e1_d15744e1_d15745e1__entry__1\">\n Type\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bmh1665703174219__table_d15743e1_d15744e1_d15745e1__entry__2\">\n Name\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bmh1665703174219__table_d15743e1_d15744e1_d15745e1__entry__3\">\n Direction\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bmh1665703174219__table_d15743e1_d15744e1_d15745e1__entry__4\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmh1665703174219__table_d15743e1_d15744e1_d15745e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">USecDrv *</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmh1665703174219__table_d15743e1_d15744e1_d15745e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">SecDrv</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmh1665703174219__table_d15743e1_d15744e1_d15745e1__entry__3\">\n INOUT\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmh1665703174219__table_d15743e1_d15744e1_d15745e1__entry__4\">Security Driver Control Structure (USecDrv) </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bmh1665703174219__topic_d93712e1_d93713e1_d93714e1_d93715e1_d93716e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d285372e135\">Return Values</h2>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"bmh1665703174219__parml_o2j_zwj_dwb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\">EntryPointFunction</dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Ffunction should return a long value that must be one of the following:</dd>\n</dl>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"bmh1665703174219__table_d15746e1_d15747e1_d15748e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Return Values for Entry Point Function</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bmh1665703174219__table_d15746e1_d15747e1_d15748e1__entry__1\">\n Return Value (long)\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bmh1665703174219__table_d15746e1_d15747e1_d15748e1__entry__2\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmh1665703174219__table_d15746e1_d15747e1_d15748e1__entry__1\"></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmh1665703174219__table_d15746e1_d15747e1_d15748e1__entry__2\">Action was successful. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmh1665703174219__table_d15746e1_d15747e1_d15748e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_INFO</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmh1665703174219__table_d15746e1_d15747e1_d15748e1__entry__2\">Action was successful and an info message is\n                        returned. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmh1665703174219__table_d15746e1_d15747e1_d15748e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_ERROR</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmh1665703174219__table_d15746e1_d15747e1_d15748e1__entry__2\">\n Something went wrong and an error message is returned. The user can decide what to do; the action can be retried or not, depending on the application context.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bmh1665703174219__p_d131981e1_d131982e1_d131983e1\">If the return value is not\n            <code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_SUCCESS</code>, the driver is also expected to fill the following members of the <code class=\"ph codeph\">USecDrv</code> structure:</p>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"bmh1665703174219__parml_v4s_2xj_dwb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\">ErrMsg</dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Info message or error message </dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\">ErrMsgLen</dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Length in bytes of info message or error message </dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\">Error</dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Info number or error number </dd>\n</dl>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bmh1665703174219__topic_d93717e1_d93718e1_d93719e1_d93720e1_d93721e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d285372e248\">Description </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bmh1665703174219__p_d131987e1_d131988e1_d131989e1\">A security driver implementation must be thread-safe. In the Uniface Router, it may be called simultaneously by several threads. Each thread will initialize the driver, and the <code class=\"ph codeph\">USecDrv</code> structure will be local to the thread.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bem1665703174291.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Security Driver Control Structure (USecDrv)</a><p>The security driver control structure is used to exchange information between the driver and the caller.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526121\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526121\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Security Driver Entry Point Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 15, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 A customized security driver must include the zsecdrv.h and specify a function to serve as an entry point for the driver. Depending on the type of security driver, other definition files should also be included. Explain this code #include \"zsecdrv.h\" #include \"usmtpsecsub.h\" #include \"unistr.h\" #include \"unienc.h\" extern long EntryPointFunction (USecDrv *SecDrv) Copy Parameters EntryPointFunction For SMTP security drivers, this can be any name. For a client/server security driver, it must be usecappl() . Type Name Direction Description USecDrv * SecDrv INOUT Security Driver Control Structure (USecDrv) Return Values EntryPointFunction Ffunction should return a long value that must be one of the following: Table 1. Return Values for Entry Point Function Return Value (long) Description Action was successful. USEC_INFO Action was successful and an info message is returned. USEC_ERROR Something went wrong and an error message is returned. The user can decide what to do; the action can be retried or not, depending on the application context. If the return value is not USEC_SUCCESS , the driver is also expected to fill the following members of the USecDrv structure: ErrMsg Info message or error message ErrMsgLen Length in bytes of info message or error message Error Info number or error number Description A security driver implementation must be thread-safe. In the Uniface Router, it may be called simultaneously by several threads. Each thread will initialize the driver, and the USecDrv structure will be local to the thread. Related Links Security Driver Control Structure (USecDrv) The security driver control structure is used to exchange information between the driver and the caller. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}